levels.desc:
**Multiple levels** Sunburst chart has a leveled structure. To make it convenient, we provide a levels option, which is an array. The first element of it is for returning to parent node when data mining. The following elements are for levels from center to outside. For example, if we don't want the data mining, and want to set the most inside sector to be red, and text to be blue, we can set the option like: 

    series: {
        // ...
        levels: [
            {
                // Blank setting for data mining
            },
            {
                // The most inside level
                itemStyle: {
                    color: 'red'
                },
                label: {
                    color: 'blue'
                }
            },
            {
                // The second level
            }
        ]
    }

